<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-N_A3a4KFML6T529HCXOO8w" name="sprint_backlog,_Q5Ki8OF8Edyp34pwdTOSVQ" guid="-N_A3a4KFML6T529HCXOO8w" changeDate="2011-01-10T02:58:22.727+0800">
  <copyrightStatement href="uma://_6Ab_EOF4Edyp34pwdTOSVQ#_4kVeYOGBEdyp34pwdTOSVQ"/>
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Items on the sprint backlog are drawn from the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../Scrum/workproducts/product_backlog_68345C16.html&quot; guid=&quot;_OZIPIOF8Edyp34pwdTOSVQ&quot;>Product Backlog&#xD;
    产品订单&lt;/a>, by the team based on the priorities set by the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../Scrum/roles/product_owner_10E7BD3.html&quot; guid=&quot;_QcnRMOF5Edyp34pwdTOSVQ&quot;>Product Owner 产品负责人&lt;/a> and the&#xD;
    team's perception of the time it will take to complete the various features.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is critical that the team selects the items and size of the sprint backlog. Because they are the ones committing to&#xD;
    completing the tasks they must be the ones to choose what they are committing to.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;div id=&quot;content&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        The sprint backlog is very commonly maintained as an Excel spreadsheet but it is also possible to use your defect&#xD;
        tracking system or any of a number of software products designed specifically for Scrum or agile. An example of the&#xD;
        Sprint Backlog in Excel looks like this:&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;Sprint backlog&quot; src=&quot;./resources/sprintbacklog.gif&quot; width=&quot;400&quot; height=&quot;188&quot; /> &#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        During the Sprint the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../Scrum/roles/scrummaster_357FCB70.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_Bw-twOF6Edyp34pwdTOSVQ&quot;>ScrumMaster Scrum主管&lt;/a> maintains the sprint backlog by updating it to reflect which&#xD;
        tasks are completed and how long the team thinks it will take to complete those that are not yet done. The&#xD;
        estimated work remaining in the sprint is calculated daily and graphed, resulting in a &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../Scrum/workproducts/sprint_burndown_chart_F647C347.html&quot; guid=&quot;_YzmSIF8sEd22Gu98eFOlrQ&quot;>Sprint&#xD;
        Burndown Chart 冲刺燃尽图&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        冲刺订单中的订单项是Scrum团队在&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../Scrum/roles/product_owner_10E7BD3.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_QcnRMOF5Edyp34pwdTOSVQ&quot;>Product Owner 产品负责人&lt;/a>给出的优先级排序基础上，并考虑了要完成这些不同的特性所需要的时间后，从&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../Scrum/workproducts/product_backlog_68345C16.html&quot; guid=&quot;_OZIPIOF8Edyp34pwdTOSVQ&quot;>Product Backlog&#xD;
        产品订单&lt;/a>中获取的。&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        由Scrum团队自己选择订单项和确定冲刺订单范围大小，是至关重要的。 因为他们是做出完成这些任务承诺的人，所以他们必须自己来选择他们将承诺完成的任务。&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        通常冲刺订单使用Excel电子表格进行维护，但是你也可以使用自己的缺陷跟踪系统或者许多其他专为Scrum或敏捷开发设计的软件产品。 一个使用Excel电子表格维护的冲刺订单的例子如下：&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;Sprint backlog&quot; src=&quot;./resources/sprintbacklog.gif&quot; width=&quot;400&quot; height=&quot;188&quot; />&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        在冲刺过程（sprint）中，Scrum主管维护和更新冲刺订单，以体现哪些任务已经完成，以及团队认为完成剩余未完成的任务还需要的时间。在冲刺（Sprint）中，每天估算剩余的工作，并使用图形化的方式予以体现，其结果就是&lt;a&#xD;
        class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../Scrum/workproducts/sprint_burndown_chart_F647C347.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_YzmSIF8sEd22Gu98eFOlrQ&quot;>Sprint Burndown Chart 冲刺燃尽图&lt;/a>。&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/div></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
